episodes.synopsis: Lucy lands in Borneo, the third-largest island in Southeast Asia, where she hopes to find the giant-nosed proboscis monkey.
episodes.title: Weirdest Monkey Alive

episodes.synopsis: Zoologist Lucy Cooke heads to the remote Australian island of Tasmania, home to some of the planet's truly odd animals, including the Tasmanian devil.
episodes.title: Devil Island

episodes.synopsis: Lucy Cooke searches South Africa for Cape vultures, sungazer girdled lizards, golden-brown baboon spiders, ground pangolins and chacma baboons.
episodes.title: Africa's Freaky Five

video.title: Freaks and Creeps
video.synopsis: Zoologist Lucy Cooke scours the planet for the world's ugliest and most unusual animals, all while promoting efforts to understand and protect them.
